<DocsPageTitle Path="Extensions/DataGrid/Features/Self Reference">
    Blazorise DataGrid: Self Reference
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    Hierarchy allows a DataGrid row to render child rows. Use a self-reference with <Code>@@ref</Code> to control expansion programmatically.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Self Reference">
        This example uses <Code>ExpandRowTrigger</Code> and <Code>ReadChildData</Code> for hierarchical rows, and calls <Code>ExpandRow</Code>, <Code>CollapseRow</Code>, <Code>ExpandAllRows</Code>, and <Code>CollapseAllRows</Code> through a DataGrid self-reference.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionContent FullWidth Outlined>
        <DataGridSelfReferenceExample />
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="DataGridSelfReferenceExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Row Editing">
        This example keeps self-reference enabled while turning on <Code>Editable</Code> rows with <Code>DataGridEditMode.Inline</Code>. Parent and child rows can both be edited.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionContent FullWidth Outlined>
        <DataGridSelfReferenceEditingExample />
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="DataGridSelfReferenceEditingExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Custom Expand Template">
        Use column <Code>ExpandTemplate</Code> when you need full control over self-reference expand rendering. The first regular column with <Code>ExpandTemplate</Code> becomes the self-reference host, and the template context exposes <Code>Item</Code>, <Code>Level</Code>, <Code>Expandable</Code>, <Code>Expanded</Code>, and <Code>Toggle()</Code>.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionContent FullWidth Outlined>
        <DataGridSelfReferenceTemplateExample />
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
    <DocsPageSectionSource Code="DataGridSelfReferenceTemplateExample" />
</DocsPageSection>

